\begin_layout Standard
Parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu=\tau hr$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma^{2}=\tau h^{2}r$
\end_inset

.
 Constant inhibitory current 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
\end_inset

 allows us to change 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

 while keeping 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma^{2}$
\end_inset

 The average current is given by 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta=\mu-\beta$
\end_inset

 and the fluctuations are given by 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma^{2}$
\end_inset

.
 Our objective is solve the characteristic equation 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
ze^{\xi}=z\cosh(z)+\xi\sinh(z)
\end{equation}

\end_inset

for 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\xi=\frac{\eta\theta}{\sigma}$
\end_inset

.
 The sign of 
\begin_inset Formula $\xi$
\end_inset

 determines the dynamical regime of the network
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\xi>0\Rightarrow\eta>0$
\end_inset

 : Drift-dominated regime 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\xi<0\Rightarrow\eta<0$
\end_inset

: Noise-dominated regime 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From the solution we can determine the eigenvalue via 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\lambda=\frac{\sigma^{2}}{2\theta}\left(z^{2}-\xi^{2}\right)
\end{equation}

\end_inset

The characteristic is solved numerically.
 Since it has infinite solutions, we need to identify the important solutions.
 Eigenvalues can be labeled
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\text{Re}(\lambda_{1})\right|<\left|\text{Re}(\lambda_{2})\right|<\ldots$
\end_inset

 according to the absolute of their real part.
 The authors first guess a start value analytically 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\xi<0$
\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula $z=i\left[2\pi n+\frac{1}{2\pi n}\left(1+\xi-e^{\xi}\pm\sqrt{(1+\xi-e^{\xi})^{2}-8\pi^{2}n^{2}(e^{\xi}-1)}\right)\right]$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\xi>0$
\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula $z=\xi+\ln\left(1+\sqrt{1-e^{-2\xi}}\right)\pm i\cdot2\pi n$
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

